1. Will there be a False Prince movie?

Things are still moving forward, and the screenplay is still being written for Paramount Pictures. It takes time to make it as awesome as I know itâ€™ll be, but no solid news yet! For those interested in seeing a movie get made, the best thing you can do is to help build enthusiasm for this series. When the fan base grows, the studioâ€™s interest in making a movie grows as well!

2. When will Book 3 be released? Whatâ€™s the title? Can you give us any hints?

Ah, the title of Book 3 is literally the biggest secret I have right now (which shows you how lame my secrets are). That title should be announced soon though. The book will probably be released sometime next spring, though I donâ€™t have an exact date yet. As to some hints, if youâ€™ve finished THE RUNAWAY KING, you have a pretty good idea of where book 3 will go. So you already have your best hint.

3. In Book 3, will the king choose Imogen or Amarinda? Will anyone important die? Will I see more of my favorite characters?

Probably. But maybe not. Those questions (and more) will definitely be answered in the third book. Or not.

4. Will there be any more books in the series?

Only three books are planned at this stage. Iâ€™m always open to writing more in this world, but I also have a great new series planned to follow this one and Iâ€™m really excited to share that story too!

5. Hmm, whatâ€™s that new series? Is it any good?

The new series is called THE PRAETOR WAR, and itâ€™s a magical alternate history of ancient Rome where an escaped slave becomes caught up in a plot to overthrow the empire. Sounds uneventful, I know, but Iâ€™ll throw in some gladiator battles, chariot races, and treks through the sewers to spice things up.

6. When will your INFINITY RING book be released?

The title isnâ€™t final, but I should have that and the cover to announce soon. The book will be released on December 1. The other books so far are excellent, so stay caught up on those so youâ€™re ready for Book 6 this winter!

7. Milk or Dark Chocolate?

Dark. Definitely, dark chocolate.

8. Will you come to my school/town/bookstore/event?

Maybe (see #7 above). See my Visits page for more information about where to begin.

Okay readers, anything else?
